<body class="body">
   <div>
      <h2 style="color: var(--text-color)">How to Protect Yourself and Your Family</h2></br>
      <h3 style="color: var(--text-color)">Cleaning</h3>
      <ul style="color: var(--text-color)">
         <li>Clean and disinfect frequently touched items daily.</li>
         <li>Disinfect anything you brought from outside your home using 90% alcohol.</li>
         <li>Regular cleaning can also help you stay organized and positive throughout this time.</li>
         <li>Keep in mind that the virus can live up to two weeks. Sanitize your parcels and packages if needed.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 style="color: var(--text-color)">Protecting Your Community</h3>
      <ul style="color: var(--text-color)">
         <li>It's important to understand that this virus brings potential risks to people around you, especially to
            elderly people and people with underlying conditions.</li>
         <li>Respect others. Practice social distancing religiously and avoid close contact if you live with high risk
            individuals.</li>
         <li><span style="font-weight: bold; color:red">ALWAYS</span> keep your mask on for your own safety and for the
            safety of others. <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=adB8RW4I3o4' style="color: black;"
               target="_blank">Click here if you are not familiar with how to properly wear a mask.</a></li>
         <li>Be honest. You should inform anyone with whom you had close contact if you test positive.</li>
         <li>Help each other. While close contact is discouraged, you can always help out people who are in need. Simple
            gestures such as dropping off groceries or calling people will help relieve their stress.</li>
      </ul>

   </div>

</body>
